{
  "stem": "13469.1",
  "chunk_idx": 3,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 2.3,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And the main thing that we do remember is the bands marching through the streets, the SS-- the SA, the brown shirts, stormtroopers, marching through the street with bands and music.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And, in fact, my brother, Ruti, he used to tag on behind like all the other children with these stormtroopers until my mother told him that he shouldn't do that because those people didn't really like us.",
      "word_count": 37
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Not really, but he says so.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And, and I believe him.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I can only remember them now based on what I see in films, really.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I, I wouldn't say that I personally could remember actually seeing them, you see.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And also we lived in this area, Neu Templehof, which was not a very Jewish area.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I've now found out that most Jews lived in, for example, Charlottenburg.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And in the middle of Berlin, there were various areas of Berlin where most of the Jews lived.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "The, the German Jews, lived in certain areas.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And the Eastern Jews, of which there were also very many in Berlin, they lived in the eastern side of Berlin.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "So-- but then where we lived, there were very few Jews in, in that particular area.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "So this is another conclusion why I think we were not very religious in those days.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And I now would imagine, I would think, that we were very assimilated Germans, really, rather than Jews, which many of the Jews were in those days.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "I mean, they started the liberal and progressive movements in Germany of Judaism.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And, and a lot of them, obviously, went further, more or less the secular Judaism, and then didn't observe any of it.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And I would've thought we were more towards that side of it.",
      "word_count": 12
    }
  ],
